63.7	Divide_and_rule	Divide and rule	In politics and sociology, divide and rule (derived from Latin: ) (also known as divide and conquer) is a combination of political, military and economic strategy of gaining and maintaining power by breaking up larger concentrations of power into chunks that individually have less power than the one implementing the strategy. The concept refers to a strategy that breaks up existing power structures and prevents smaller power groups from linking up.	
